<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3390] TTornado server doesn&apos;t handle closed connections properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3390</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Tornado Thrift server uses a TTornadoStreamTransport that uses Tornado&apos;s IOStream to handle incoming connections. The main method for handling this is a while loop in  `handle_stream` that waits for incoming data. This works fine until the client decides to stop the connection in which case TTransportException.END_OF_FILE is raised. This exception is expected behaviour and should be caught appropriately in `handle_stream`.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12905542">THRIFT-3390</key>
            <summary>TTornado server doesn&apos;t handle closed connections properly</summary>
