                            <comment id="14960757" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 16 Oct 2015 14:09:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user c4urself opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/654&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/654&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3390&quot; title=&quot;TTornado server doesn&amp;#39;t handle closed connections properly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-3390&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-3390&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Tornado server should gracefully handle closed connections&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    If END_OF_FILE exception is met the Tornado server should just break&lt;br/&gt;
